If you have not installed ASP.NET Core before the process of getting started is pretty straight forward.

The stes I take are geared towards users on Mac OS X. It's even easier on Windows.

Step 1: Install Mono
http://www.mono-project.com/docs/getting-started/install/mac/

Step 2: Install Visual Studio Code
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs?dv=osx

Step 3:Install ASP.NET Core
Head over to https://get.asp.net/ At the time of this post the link will down load DNX-1.0.0-rc1-update1.pkg


 